90,IssuesEvent,2016-07-11 12:56:55+00:00,48198706,dschep/ntfy,667763,dschep,,,closed,Telegram support,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dschep/ntfy/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],1,"ntfy is nifty. Are you interested in adding support for [Telegram](https://telegram.org/)? I made a [package](https://github.com/rahiel/telegram-send) that could be used. It has a `configure` function to guide users in setting it up and a `send` function to send stuff.
```python
conf = ""~/.config/ntfy/telegram-send.conf""
telegram_send.configure(conf)
telegram_send.send(messages=[""hello""], conf=conf)
```
That call to `configure` saves the credentials (api token, and which user to send messages to) in the `conf` file and the call to `send` uses it to send a message.

I'd like to help if you're interested.",{},{}
