642,IssuesEvent,2015-03-11 22:08:12+00:00,18464187,jquast/wcwidth,2913679,stevengj,,,opened,wrong width for U+00AD,[],[],0,"Hi, I was looking at your `wcwidth` library for comparison, since in the utf8proc library we are also implementing a similar feature (see JuliaLang/utf8proc#2).   The first disagreement that I came across between your implementation and ours was for [U+00AD (soft hyphen)](http://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/char/00ad/index.htm), where you seem to give `1`
```python
>>> from wcwidth import wcwidth
>>> wcwidth(unichr(173))
1
```
and we give zero (a [soft hyphen](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soft_hyphen) is used for line breaking, but is ordinarily not printed).  In general, we return 0 for most characters in category Cf (formatting control characters).   The `wcwidth` function on MacOS 10.10.2 also returns `-1` (not printable) for this code point.",{},{}
