653,IssuesEvent,2018-08-02 15:21:16+00:00,11745275,mikedh/trimesh,5444873,david-zwicker,,,opened,Bug in Trimesh.voxelized,[],[],0,"I discovered a problem when voxelizing complex geometries ([nasal_cavity.ply.zip](https://github.com/mikedh/trimesh/files/2254037/nasal_cavity.ply.zip)). The problem is visible in the following comparison of the original geometry (shown in red) and the voxelized geometry shown translucently in gray:

![voxels](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5444873/43593437-03a1c268-9678-11e8-970a-9d42e5791060.png)

Apparently, the voxelization adds vertical bands that are not present in the original geometry. The code I used to generate the voxelization is

```python
mesh = trimesh.load('nasal_cavity.ply')
print(mesh.is_watertight)
mesh_discretized = mesh.voxelized(pitch=1, max_iter=None)
voxels = mesh_discretized.marching_cubes
voxels.export('nasal_cavity_voxels.ply')
```

I also tried different values for `pitch` and I used `method='ray'`, but I observed similar effects for all settings. Is there any hope to achieve a proper voxelization of this geometry?
",{},{}
