2780,IssuesEvent,2015-08-04 13:43:04+00:00,15764568,maxtepkeev/python-redmine,7230566,dlmueller,,,opened,Cannot get generated Index by Title page,[],[],0,"Let https://redmine.example.com be my Redmine instance and ""myproject"" the ```project_id``` of my project with a wiki containing at least the page ""somepage"". With the following code I'm able to get the content of that page using the REST-API (presumably via https://redmine.example.com/projects/myproject/wiki/somepage.json):

```python
from redmine import Redmine
redmine = Redmine(""https://redmine.example.com"", key = ""..."")
page = redmine.wiki_page.get(""somepage"", project_id = ""myproject"")
``` 

Now Redmine offers two special index pages:
* Index by Title
* Index by Date

### Index by Title

HTML = https://redmine.example.com/projects/myproject/wiki/index
JSON = https://redmine.example.com/projects/myproject/wiki/index.json
XML = https://redmine.itz.uni-halle.de/projects/dienst-email/wiki/index.xml


With ```python-redmine 1.2.0``` on ```Python 2.7.6``` and ```Redmine 2.4.2.stable``` I'm not able to fetch that Index by Title wiki page. Instead I'm getting the following KeyError exception:

```python
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""<stdin>"", line 1, in <module>
  File ""/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/redmine/managers.py"", line 127, in get
    return self.resource_class(self, self.retrieve()[0])
  File ""/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/redmine/managers.py"", line 71, in retrieve
    if isinstance(response[self.container], dict):
KeyError: 'wiki_page'
```

### Index by Date

HTML = https://redmine.example.com/projects/myproject/wiki/date_index
JSON = *not available on Redmine 2.4.2.stable*
XML = *not available on Redmine 2.4.2.stable - either with intent or due to a bug*

The JSON/XML versions of that page might be unavailable either with intent or due to a bug. Perhaps that issue is already fixed in newer versions of Redmine. But that's another story ...",{},{}
