3412,IssuesEvent,2018-08-17 21:44:48+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,1208642,nswamy,47359,apache,closed,Different Results Generated from 0.10.1 MXNET R Package and 0.9.4 MXNET R Package,"[{'id': 794466360, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3OTQ0NjYzNjA=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apache/incubator-mxnet/labels/Pending%20Requester%20Info', 'name': 'Pending Requester Info', 'color': 'd93f0b', 'default': False}, {'id': 270131542, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwyNzAxMzE1NDI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apache/incubator-mxnet/labels/R', 'name': 'R', 'color': '0052cc', 'default': False}]",[],7,"Dear Users and Developers,
 
I worked in a project about data mining which using convolutional neural networks based on MXNET R package. And when I use the old version of MXNET R package 0.9.4, I got a pretty good result. However, the error rate generated by updated version( 0.10.1) was two times higher than the error rate generated by old version (0.9.4). I had checked the source code in github (https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/tree/master/R-package), and found that developers added more mx functions, more parameters in some functions. So I guess that maybe these cause the differences between two results generated by old version package and updated version package. Also, I kept the same random seeds on the top of my codes. 

My question is that whether there are some errors/mistakes in old MXNET R package? 

Thanks!
Best",{},{}
3422,IssuesEvent,2017-09-28 17:29:59+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,1690881,phunterlau,47359,apache,closed,small amount memory cost in GPU device 0 even if context is set to mx.gpu(1),[],[],1,"I just noticed that running mx.mod.Module.fit can produce a small amount GPU memory cost in device 0 even if I set context to mx.gpus(1) when creating the mx.mod.Module variable(`mod = mx.mod.Module(context=mx.gpu(1), symbol=net)`).

The problem seems to be caused at line 410 in python/mxnet/module/module.py when it tries to copy initialized local parameters to kvstore(). I loaded my pre-trained weights using `mx.nd.load` which means these parameters are stored in cpu originally. Thus, when copying them to kv-store, they are copied to mx.gpu(0) by default.

I am not sure if it is a bug or so. But maybe we should check and transfer arg_params/aux_params to the target device in mx.mod.Module.init_params?",{},{}
3452,IssuesEvent,2016-05-07 11:39:27+00:00,33884891,apache/incubator-airflow,4282712,bolkedebruin,47359,apache,closed,"prevent using SQLite db with LocalExecutor, CeleryExecutor","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apache/incubator-airflow/labels/Enhancement', 'name': 'Enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apache/incubator-airflow/labels/Help%20Wanted', 'name': 'Help Wanted', 'color': '159818'}]",[],1,"In hindsight, it was perhaps silly of me to try to run the LocalExecutor with a sqlite database, but it seemed to work.

