3858,IssuesEvent,2018-01-19 22:10:54+00:00,648332,assimp/assimp,4348571,mvidiassov,265533,assimp,opened,RT-extension not found under Mac OS,[],[],0,"code/CMakelist.txt looks for RT functions like clock_gettime in librt, unless the compiler is MSVC.
Since RT-extension in Mac OS is in the system library (libc), it is not found.
The extension was introduced in Mac OS 10.12, headers for it come with Xcode 8.

I have no suggestion on how to fix the problem properly since I do not know what is proper Assimp approach, for example is cross-compiling Assimp in current environment, but targeting older version of Mac OS a supported scenario?
May be as a workaround some cmake option can be introduced so that the user  will be able to make the choice himself without editing code/CMakelist.txt?",{},{}
