4453,IssuesEvent,2015-07-11 22:03:21+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,45071,stefanv,897180,scikit-image,opened,"In `skimage.draw`, y, x instead of r, c convention is used",[],[],0,,{},{}
4464,IssuesEvent,2015-01-22 08:34:09+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,492549,jni,897180,scikit-image,closed,Incorrect return types for some morphological operations,[],[],2,"Our morphology operations are a bit of a mess. Three particular examples stand out:

- `binary_*` call out to scipy's `ndimage.convolve` and then does some arithmetic on the output to determine the dilation. Amazingly, this appears to be slower than just calling out to scipy's ndimage morphological operations.
- In the same vein, our result is a uint8 image. I think this is quite egregious because with the name `binary` users (ie me) might expect that we return a bool, as scipy's functions do.
- Finally, our greyscale morphological operations start by converting all images to uint8, thereby throwing away range information that users might very much be interested in.

See also #1070.",{},{}
