4561,IssuesEvent,2018-06-25 19:13:00+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,15566,rhyolight,1039191,numenta,closed,Swap out pcre when std::regex has sufficient support and leave all platforms on pcre for now. ,"[{'id': 119506191, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwxMTk1MDYxOTE=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic.core/labels/priority:3', 'name': 'priority:3', 'color': '009800', 'default': False}, {'id': 78895824, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3ODg5NTgyNA==', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic.core/labels/type:cleanup', 'name': 'type:cleanup', 'color': '006b75', 'default': False}, {'id': 378142579, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzNzgxNDI1Nzk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic.core/labels/under-review', 'name': 'under-review', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}, {'id': 170603192, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwxNzA2MDMxOTI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic.core/labels/windows', 'name': 'windows', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]",[],2,"We did have PCRE working on Windows. But at the time there were comments about not wanting to pollute the repo with an OS specific library. We moved to `std::regex` to be able to remove that library. 

However to avoid avoid platform special-casing, it's better we swap out `pcre` when `std::regex` has sufficient support and leave all platforms on `pcre` for now. 

Original discussion:
https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/pull/275#discussion-diff-23797195R51
",{},{}
