4607,IssuesEvent,2015-11-06 14:26:54+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,633680,jalavik,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,BibMatch: make query formats sane,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_BibMatch', 'name': 'c_BibMatch', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_minor', 'name': 'p_minor', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/r_wontfix', 'name': 'r_wontfix', 'color': 'bfe5bf'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],2,"Originally on 2013-01-30

Right now when using BibMatch you can define BibConvert style syntax when you want to transform record values into a format better suited for searching. For example, stripping certain symbols or removing ambiguous words.

This syntax can be quite crazy sometimes, for example a common author search may look like this:

`[100__a::REP(COMMA,;;)::LIMW(;;,R)::REP(;;,)::REP( , author:)::SHAPE::ADD(author:,)]*`

Yeah, I know, its insane, but it does the job in translating a value like ""John Ellis"" from `100__a` in a record into ""author:Ellis*"" more suitable for searching.

To make this more user friendly it would be nice if we could make more useful functions available with smarter syntax. I will come back with suggestions on how later.

However, the usage of these functions could then be mapped to certain fields etc. either globally or one-shot like.",{},{}
