5168,IssuesEvent,2016-02-22 12:52:18+00:00,38744670,zalando/patroni,3407345,CyberDem0n,1564818,zalando,closed,Zookeeper/exhibitor support is broken,[],[],5,"When trying to deploy with Zookeeper (using `EXHIBITOR_HOSTS` / `EXHIBITOR_PORT`).

From `senza` template:
```
      TaupageConfig:
        ...
        etcd_discovery_domain: """"
        environment:
          SCOPE: ""{{Arguments.version}}""
          ETCD_DISCOVERY_DOMAIN: """"
          EXHIBITOR_HOSTS: 172.31.xxx.xxx
          EXHIBITOR_PORT: 2181
```

I'm getting this:
```
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:   File ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/patroni/__init__.py"", line 37, in get_dcs
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:     return ZooKeeper(name, config['zookeeper'])
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:   File ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/patroni/zookeeper.py"", line 83, in __init__
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:     self.exhibitor = ExhibitorEnsembleProvider(exhibitor['hosts'], exhibitor['port'], poll_interval=interval)
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:   File ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/patroni/zookeeper.py"", line 32, in __init__
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:     while not self.poll():
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:   File ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/patroni/zookeeper.py"", line 40, in poll
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:     json = self._query_exhibitors(self._exhibitors)
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:   File ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/patroni/zookeeper.py"", line 55, in _query_exhibitors
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:     random.shuffle(exhibitors)
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:   File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/random.py"", line 289, in shuffle
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]:     x[i], x[j] = x[j], x[i]
 Feb 22 11:22:39 ip-172-31-137-170 docker/537ee34cb131[843]: TypeError: 'str' object does not support item assignment
```

The cause seems to be that `postgres_ha.sh` doesn't try hard enough to make `hosts` an actual list:
```
    if [[ -n $EXHIBITOR_HOSTS && -n $EXHIBITOR_PORT ]]; then
      cat >> postgres.yml <<__EOF__
  exhibitor:
    poll_interval: 300
    port: ${EXHIBITOR_PORT}
    hosts: ${EXHIBITOR_HOSTS}
__EOF__
    fi
```
",{},{}
