5343,IssuesEvent,2018-04-14 15:04:14+00:00,59868262,aws/chalice,8852,jhw,2232217,aws,closed,Terrible Lambda performance for CPU- bound function,[],[],4,"Hi, I have a Chalice project with a number of endpoints/functions, working fine, no problem. I recently added an extra function which performs a calculation on the server - POST a JSON request, perform calculation, return JSON response. The calculation is totally stateless, ie lambda function doesn't call any third party URLs or datastore or anything. On my laptop the calculation takes ~1 second. On lambda the average time is ~14 seconds!  This isn't going to work for me. I don't think it's the API Gateway or the startup time at fault as all the other functions in the project (non- CPU bound) return nice timely results. It feels to me like the calculation is being run on a tiny machine or maybe there is limited memory. I have tried setting ""memory_size"" in .chalice/config.json to 512, but makes no difference. Can anyone suggest how I might improve performance of the calculation, possibly by increasing memory (perhaps I am doing it wrong ?) or somehow specifying a larger machine (is that possible ?) - Thx!",{},{}
