5833,IssuesEvent,2015-07-14 14:27:19+00:00,8372403,snowballstem/snowball,230044,dainiusjocas,3676704,snowballstem,opened,Java class generation,[],[],0,"I'm working on a stemmer for Lithuanian language. Stemmer is going to be used in Lucene based search engine, therefore I need to use the generated Java class. 

In my algorithm I'm using the length of the word and I believe this causes me a problem.

I've been following this [tutorial](http://snowball.tartarus.org/runtime/use.html). The resulting Java class works fine with the example program. But Java code does not compile for using in it Lucene with this problem:
```
[...] /src/main/java/org/tartarus/snowball/ext/LithuanianStemmer.java:[589,27] error: current has private access in SnowballProgram
```
I see that the code which was generated by snowball compiler tries to get length of the string in this way:
```
(current.length());
```

Unfortunatelly, the implementation of `SnowballProgram` class that is used by [Lucene](https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/lucene/dev/trunk/lucene/analysis/common/src/java/org/tartarus/snowball/SnowballProgram.java) has defined `current` field in this way 
```
 // current string
    private char current[];
```

So, if I want to use the generated class in Lucene, I have to manually change the call for string length in this way:
```
getCurrent().length();
```

Am I facing a bug? Or this is the expected behaviour?",{},{}
5846,IssuesEvent,2015-09-11 00:49:40+00:00,22978655,googlemaps/google-maps-services-python,116385,stephenmcd,3717923,googlemaps,closed,retry fails when using enterprise credentials,[],[],1,"Retrying a Client._get() with enterprise credentials (without a key) raises a ValueError [in _generate_auth_url](https://github.com/googlemaps/google-maps-services-python/blob/master/googlemaps/client.py#L231). It looks like this is due to a positional param issue in _get(), where accepts_clientid should be passed but [extract_body is passed in its place](https://github.com/googlemaps/google-maps-services-python/blob/master/googlemaps/client.py#L176).

Please let me know if you need a more specific test case, or if a pull request would help.",{},{}
