5912,IssuesEvent,2017-10-24 12:18:05+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,374612,benjaoming,3926525,learningequality,opened,"Swap steps 2, 3 and 4 in setup wizard","[{'id': 492821376, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/DEV:%20frontend', 'name': 'DEV: frontend', 'color': 'DFDFDF', 'default': False}, {'id': 492816719, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/TASK:%20ux%20update', 'name': 'TASK: ux update', 'color': 'E2D1E0', 'default': False}]",[],0,"### Observed behavior

Setup wizard is:

**Please select the default language for Kolibri** => **Name your Facility** => **Create your Admin account** => **Choose a Facility setup**

### Expected behavior

**Please select the default language for Kolibri** => **Choose a Facility setup** => **Name your Facility** => **Create your Admin account**

Because the type of facility chosen may guide the kinds of questions and help texts in the remainder of the wizard, we should move the question to the beginning.

Moving **Choose a Facility setup** to the beginning means that when we as users to **Name your Facility**, the choice of name is more easily understood because the wizard has exposed roughly which types of facilities Kolibri has to do with.

Finally, moving **Create your Admin account** to Step 4 will mean that the admin can log in fresh after choosing her password.

### User-facing consequences

Mainly it's the perception of what a facility is I worry about.",{},{}
