6465,IssuesEvent,2016-05-10 12:22:20+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,38393,msarahan,6392739,conda,closed,'noarch_python' and header files,[],[],1,"I made a conda-forge recipe for pybind11, which is producing platform-dependent packages. 

I think that pybind11 should be a `noarch_python` package. It does not hold any binaries and has a universal pypi wheel.

The issue is that it holds headers (it is a header-only library), plus some pure python. `noarch_python` does not support the case where there are headers.",{},{}
