bash: /bin/sh: Argument list too long
bash: /bin/sh: Argument list too long
```

After this, my `$PS1` is completely wiped, and all further bash commands give the same ""argument list is too long"" error. 

Downgrading to conda 4.0.8 fixes it. 

Before it did this and was completely broken, I also noticed that `CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV` was giving the full path to the env, instead of the short version, which broke my custom `PS1`. Should I open a separate issue for that? ",{},{}
