6506,IssuesEvent,2015-01-09 16:19:42+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,4965260,cehbrecht,6392739,conda,opened,conda update breaks if xxd (from vim-common) is not installed,[],[],0,"after updating conda today on a minimal centos image the conda installation was broken. Python complained about problems with md5.

This probably happened because a postinstall script did not run because ""xxd"" was missing. The xxd program is part of the package vim-common. So installing vim-common first (sudo yum install vim-common) and then updating conda works.

