6962,IssuesEvent,2017-12-19 16:36:11+00:00,94331757,bethgelab/foolbox,6177693,wielandbrendel,7590370,bethgelab,closed,"When checking the bound of the image, the preprocessed offset is not added back. ",[],[],7,"   in this line https://github.com/bethgelab/foolbox/blob/master/foolbox/adversarial.py#L226, you check whether the adversarial image is within bound or not, but we should add the offset back first. Currently I constantly receive ""error message about assert not strict or self.in_bounds(image)"". 
