7225,IssuesEvent,2017-12-08 17:38:34+00:00,68926339,CMA-ES/pycma,7316439,nikohansen,9052298,CMA-ES,opened,maxstd and minstd are in conflict,[],[],0,"In particular if these values are set close to each other, they cannot necessarily be satisfied at the same time, because the global `sigma` is used for both corrections. This could be easily fixed in the `CMA_diagonal` setting, where diagonal corrections are unproblematic. With full covariance matrix this is rather a feature than a bug, because the change size of a diagonal change is non-trivial to compute. Alternatively to adjust `maxstd`, the axis/axes with the largest projection could be shortened.

As a side note, decreasing `sigma` to set `maxstd` seems only a good idea if it corrects for a previous increase of `sigma`.",{},{}
