7336,IssuesEvent,2016-03-21 20:49:21+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,5740946,alexlauerman,9289019,letsencrypt,opened,letsencrypt_apache/configurator.py finds zero vhosts,[],[],0,"[Line 720](https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/01608d4d8d0a23578d3509799a597d0272513a40/letsencrypt-apache/letsencrypt_apache/configurator.py#L720) of letsencrypt_apache/configurator.py finds zero vhosts when it looks at /etc/apache2/apache2-le-ssl.conf (the file it creates by calling _copy_create_ssl_vhost_skeleton). 

Here are the last few lines of my apache2.conf:
```
<VirtualHost *:80>
   ServerAdmin alex@trustfoundry.net
   DocumentRoot /var/www
   ServerAlias trustfoundry.net
</VirtualHost>
```

The statement that gets entered, and error that gets output is on lines [723 through 725](https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/01608d4d8d0a23578d3509799a597d0272513a40/letsencrypt-apache/letsencrypt_apache/configurator.py#L723,L725):
```
Error: should only be one vhost in /etc/apache2/apache2.conf 
Currently, we only support configurations with one vhost per file
```


- I have confirmed that zero ""VirtualHost"" matches are found.
- I have confirmed the file gets created.
- I have also confirmed that it does correctly find one vhost if I pass in avail_fp as the file to search, which is /etc/apache2/apache2.conf. 
