8629,IssuesEvent,2017-05-10 19:47:27+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,3270755,adeverteuil,17889013,certbot,opened,tls-sni-01 with the manual plugin,[],[],0,"Hello,

I'd like to extend the manual plugin to support the tls-sni-01 authentication protocol. Is there already an effort ongoing for this? Has this been discussed in the past?

I understand that tls-sni is a less popular challenge to perform manually, but I already have a working proof of concept using hook scripts.

My use case is we are managing load balancers and different projects demand different LB methods. Some are layer 4, some are layer 7, so http-01 is not always feasible. If I want to implement one ACME authentication method, it's going to be TLS-SNI, since it doesn't matter if port 80 is proxied or NATted. And if a client wants layer 4 load balancing on port 443 also, then we won't be doing SSL offloading in the first place.

Here's my concept and use case in more details:
https://alexandre.deverteuil.net/blogue/letsencrypt-tls-sni/

If such feature is not in the short term roadmap but would still be welcome, I would like to work on it and issue a pull request.

Thanks.",{},{}
