8764,IssuesEvent,2018-06-08 12:05:42+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,587021,andrevmatos,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Switch to eth_sign-compatible signatures in core and SCs,"[{'id': 318426947, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzMTg0MjY5NDc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 465306362, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0NjUzMDYzNjI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/good_to_have', 'name': 'good_to_have', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}, {'id': 473078399, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0NzMwNzgzOTk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/needs%20discussion', 'name': 'needs discussion', 'color': 'f9d0c4', 'default': False}, {'id': 568592923, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw1Njg1OTI5MjM=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/smart_contract', 'name': 'smart_contract', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}]",[],0,"## Problem Definition

We currently sign messages on Raiden simply by signing the hash of the message. By using [eth_sign_sha3](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/2df06259496fd10cadd29c8e3f4f5f86289f3940/raiden/utils/__init__.py#L57-L64) as default hasher, and changing the smartcontracts accordingly (should as simple as prepending the prefix before `keccak256` it), we should make all our signing compatible with `eth_sign` RPC interface.

Of course, it doesn't mean we fully support this standard, but as the changes are minimal, it could allow us to fully use a web3 signer middleware, and **possibly** add in the future the option of doing all signing on the eth-node side, getting rid of opening the private key in the Raiden node, and easily switching to eip712 signatures when finished.",{},{}
