8817,IssuesEvent,2017-04-07 10:27:25+00:00,1732211,FactoryBoy/factory_boy,694541,rbarrois,20368050,FactoryBoy,opened,"Reduce the amount of warnings, eventually switching to `-Werror`",[],[],0,"Our code tends to send lots of warnings:
- About deprecated Python / mongoengine / Django features
- About unclosed files

We should remove most of those, ideally without too many hacks.
This would allow us to change our test setup to use `-Werror`, i.e to crash on deprecation warnings — thus adapting to new APIs as soon as they arrive instead of waiting until the old ones disappear.",{},{}
